                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-805" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL GREEN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a web and brace manufacturer, and live in Shoe-lane, Holborn. The prisoner took two rooms at my factory, No. 24, Wilks-street, Spitalfields—he came there on the 3rd of December—on the 10th of January, I missed some bobbins, some slays, and some battens—I spoke to the prisoner about it on the evening of the 10th of January—he said he would confess the truth, if I would forgive him—I said it would be better for him—he said he had done it through distress—that he had left some bobbins at Rondean's, and meant to get them again.</p>
